{{italic title}}
'''''El Adalid''''' was a [[Catholic]] weekly newspaper published from [[Torrelavega]], [[Spain]], between 1906 and 1917.<ref>Garrido Mart<U+00ED>n, Aurora. ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=sT6e7RrY6FMC&pg=PA161 Cantabria 1902-1923: elecciones y partidos pol<U+00ED>ticos]''. [Santander]: Universidad de Cantabria, 1990. p. 161</ref><ref name="b1">Cueva Merino, Julio de la. ''[http://books.google.com/books?id=wO3QgjbOb5sC&pg=PA90 Clericales y anticlericales: el conflicto entre confesionalidad y secularizaci<U+00F3>n en Cantabria (1875-1923)]''. [Santander]: Universidad de Cantabria, 1994. pp. 90-91</ref> 

==History and profile==
The first issue of ''El Adalid'' was published on 19 March 1906 and was directed by Ceferino Calder<U+00F3>n.<ref name="b1"/><ref>''[http://books.google.com/books?id=hFExAQAAMAAJ Raz<U+00F3>n y fe: Revista hispano-americana de cultura]'', Vol. 15. Compa<U+00F1><U+00ED>a de Jes<U+00FA>s, 1906. p. 133</ref> 

The newspaper was the most militant Catholic publication in [[Cantabria]].<ref name="b1"/> ''El Adalid'' had a traditionalist editorial line, and denounced [[liberalism]] as 'the banner of [[Lucifer]]'.<ref>S<U+00E1>nchez G<U+00F3>mez, Miguel A. ''[http://books.google.se/books?id=Kake_AY-iuIC&pg=PA388 Torrelavega: tres siglos de hist<U+00F3>ria : an<U+00E1>lisis de un crecimiento desequilibrado]''. [Santander]: Universidad de Cantabria, 1995. p. 388</ref> The Catholic Electoral Centre was formed around ''El Adalid'' and the newspaper was an important cornerstone in the campaign to elect Jos<U+00E9> Mar<U+00ED>a Guti<U+00E9>rrez Calder<U+00F3>n as provincial deputy in its year of foundation.<ref>S<U+00E1>nchez G<U+00F3>mez, Miguel A. ''[http://books.google.se/books?id=Kake_AY-iuIC&pg=PA320 Torrelavega: tres siglos de hist<U+00F3>ria : an<U+00E1>lisis de un crecimiento desequilibrado]''. [Santander]: Universidad de Cantabria, 1995. p. 320</ref>

''El Besaya'' (published 1918-1919) was launched as a substitute to ''El Adalid''. However, ''El Besaya'' had a more modernist approach that ''El Adalid''.<ref>S<U+00E1>nchez G<U+00F3>mez, Miguel A. ''[http://books.google.se/books?id=Kake_AY-iuIC&pg=PA324 Torrelavega: tres siglos de hist<U+00F3>ria : an<U+00E1>lisis de un crecimiento desequilibrado]''. [Santander]: Universidad de Cantabria, 1995. pp. 17, 324</ref>

